items.title: The 'truth serum' for AI: OpenAI’s new method for training models to confess their mistakes
items.summary: OpenAI researchers have introduced a novel method that acts as a truth serum for large language models . The technique, " addresses a growing concern in enterprise AI: Models can be dishonest . When a model misbehaves, it is significantly more likely to admit it in the confession than in its main answer . For real-world applications, this technique evolves the creation of more transparent and steerable AI systems .

items.title: AWS launches Kiro powers with Stripe, Figma, and Datadog integrations for AI-assisted coding
items.summary: Amazon Web Services introduces Kiro powers, a system that lets developers give their AI assistants instant, specialized expertise in specific tools and workflows . The launch includes partnerships with nine technology companies . The capability marks a departure from how most AI coding tools work today . Each connection loads dozens of tool definitions into the AI's working memory before writing a single line of code .

items.title: Gong study: Sales teams using AI generate 77% more revenue per rep
items.summary: Seven in ten enterprise revenue leaders now trust AI to regularly inform their business decisions . Organizations that have embedded AI into their core go-to-market strategies are 65 percent more likely to increase their win rates than competitors still treating the technology as optional . The number of U.S. companies using AI for forecasting and measuring strategic initiatives jumped 50 percent year over year .

items.title: GAM takes aim at “context rot”: A dual-agent memory architecture that outperforms long-context LLMs
items.summary: A new paper introduces general agentic memory (GAM) a system built to preserve long-horizon information without overwhelming the model . The core premise is simple: Split memory into two specialized roles, one that captures everything, another that retrieves exactly the right things at the right moment . As conversations grow long, older information gets truncated, summarized or silently dropped .

items.title: Inside NetSuite’s next act: Evan Goldberg on the future of AI-powered business systems
items.summary: NetSuite was the first company to deliver enterprise applications entirely through web browsers . It combined CRM, ERP, and ecommerce into one unified platform . Next represents a quantum leap — contextual, conversational, agentic, composable AI becoming an extension of operations, not separate tools . It autonomously reconciles accounts, optimizes payment timing, predicts cash crunches, and surfaces reasoning at every step .

items.title: We Got Claude to Fine-Tune an Open Source LLM
items.summary: We Got Claude to Fine-Tune an Open Source LLM . We got Claude to fine-tune an open-source LLM for the first time . We're happy to have Claude working on a new version of the LLM that can be used in the next generation of LLMs . We'll see more of Claude's work in the coming weeks .

items.title: Nvidia's new AI framework trains an 8B model to manage tools like a pro
items.summary: Researchers at Nvidia and the University of Hong Kong have released Orchestrator, an 8-billion-parameter model that coordinates different tools and large language models to solve complex problems . The model achieved higher accuracy at a lower cost than much larger models in tool-use benchmarks, while aligning with user preferences . The findings suggest that this composite approach could pave the way for more practical and scalable AI reasoning systems in the enterprise .

items.title: Use Circle to Search and Google Lens to spot scam messages.
items.summary: You can now use Circle to Search and Google Lens to detect scammy messages you receive on your phone . You can also use Google Lens and Circle to search for messages on the phone .
